Citation.sTitle: Influence of the Temperature on the Liquid-Liquid-Solid Equilibria of the Ternary System Water + Ethanol + 1-Decanol
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid-liquid equilibrium data for the ternary system water + ethanol + 1-decanol have been measured at (2, 15, and 25) deg C, with two different methods of analysis: refractive index and gas chromatography. A small region with three phases (solid-liquid-liquid) and two regions with two phases (solid-liquid) appear at 2 deg C. Liquid-liquid regions show quite similar shapes at all of the temperatures.
